com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.dom.events

Interface DOMEvent

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DOMKeyEvent, DOMMouseEvent, DOMUIEvent, DOMUIEventModifier 

    public interface DOMEvent
    Represents DOM event and provides access to the event data.
    表示DOM事件，并提供对事件数据的访问。

    • Method Summary

      All Methods  Instance Methods  Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      DOMEventTarget getCurrentTarget()
      Returns the DOMEventTarget whose DOMEventListeners are currently being processed.
      返回当前正在处理其DOMEventListener的DOMEventTarget。
      DOMEventPhase getEventPhase()
      Used to indicate which phase of event flow is currently being evaluated.
      用于指示当前正在评估事件流的哪个阶段。
      DOMEventTarget getTarget()
      Returns the DOMEventTarget to which the event was originally dispatched.
      返回事件最初分配到的DOMEventTarget。
      DOMEventType getType()
      Returns the type of this DOM event.
      返回此DOM事件的类型。
      boolean isBubbles()
      Used to indicate whether or not an event is a bubbling event.
      用于指示事件是否为冒泡事件。
      boolean isCancelable()
      Used to indicate whether or not an event can have its default action prevented.
      用于指示事件是否可以阻止其默认操作。
      boolean isKeyboardEvent()
      Indicates whether the event is a DOMKeyEvent and it can be cast to this type to get more information about key event.
      指示事件是否为DOMKeyEvent，可以将其强制转换为此类型以获得有关键事件的更多信息。
      boolean isMouseEvent()
      Indicates whether the event is a DOMMouseEvent and it can be cast to this type to get more information about mouse event.
      指示事件是否为DOMMouseEvent，可以将其强制转换为此类型以获得有关鼠标事件的更多信息。
      boolean isUIEvent()
      Indicates whether the event is a DOMUIEvent and it can be cast to this type to get more information about mouse event.
      指示事件是否为DOMUIEvent，可以将其强制转换为此类型以获取有关鼠标事件的更多信息。
      void preventDefault()
      Cancels the event if it is cancelable, without stopping further propagation of the event.
      如果可以取消事件，则将其取消，而不停止事件的进一步传播。
      void stopPropagation()
      Prevents further propagation of the current event.
      防止当前事件进一步传播。

      • isMouseEvent

        Indicates whether the event is a DOMMouseEvent and it can be cast to this type to get more information about mouse event.
        指示事件是否为DOMMouseEvent，可以将其强制转换为此类型以获得有关鼠标事件的更多信息。

      • isKeyboardEvent

        boolean isKeyboardEvent()
        Indicates whether the event is a DOMKeyEvent and it can be cast to this type to get more information about key event.

        Returns:
        true if the event is a DOMKeyEvent. 如果事件是。

      • isBubbles

        boolean isBubbles()
        Used to indicate whether or not an event is a bubbling event. If the event can bubble the value is true, else the value is false.
        用于指示事件是否为冒泡事件。如果事件可以冒泡，则该值为true，否则该值为false。

      • isCancelable

        boolean isCancelable()
        Used to indicate whether or not an event can have its default action prevented. If the default action can be prevented the value is true, else the value is false.
        用于指示事件是否可以阻止其默认操作。如果可以阻止默认操作，则该值为true，否则为false。

      • preventDefault

        void preventDefault()
        Cancels the event if it is cancelable, without stopping further propagation of the event.
        如果可以取消事件，则将其取消，而不停止事件的进一步传播。

      • stopPropagation

        void stopPropagation()
        Prevents further propagation of the current event.
        防止当前事件进一步传播。
